  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      1. Access the optimal cut point value of copeptin which predicts development of central
           diabetes insipidus postoperatively with highest accuracy.

        2. Access the optimal cut point value of copeptin which predicts the lack of central
           diabetes insipidus postoperatively with highest accuracy

        3. Access the relative change in copeptin values between baseline and post-surgery as a
           predictor for diabetes insipidus development.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patient serum levels of copeptin would be measured after phlebotomy of 3 ml of blood in EDTA
      tube twice a) within 1-4 hours of extubation and b) within 4-24 hours of extubation (the
      morning following surgery).
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
